article.headline: Valparaiso 77, Centenary 66
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Dan Oppland scored 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds as Valparaiso led the entire game in beating Centenary 77-66 on Thursday night. The Crusaders (7-9, 4-3 Mid-Continent Conference) shot 55 percent from the field (28-51) and extended their winning streak to three games, despite a 32-point performance by Centenary's Andrew Wisniewski. Valparaiso took an early 21-12 lead and held a 36-27 advantage at the half. The Crusaders extended their lead to 48-29 before the Gents closed to within five points, 60-55, with 7:27 remaining. Centenary (9-8, 3-3) got no closer the rest of the way. Joaquim Gomes scored 11 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for Valparaiso, which also got 13 points from Oumar Sylla and 12 from Ali Berdiel. Wisniewski finished 11-for-21 from the field and 6-for-9 from 3-point range. Rickey Evans added 14 points and six rebounds for Centenary. Valparaiso outscored Centenary in the paint 38-24.
